sign_text:
The cauldron boils, stirring wind and waves;
A lone boat must cross the rushing river.
Cleverness hides clumsiness within;
Human affairs turn to wasted time.

When hearts are in harmony,
matters are understood;
Outside the gate, efforts bear fruit;
Even tangled affairs will have an end.

One peach, one plum, one spring anew;
Who recalls the fresh scene once in view?
By woods and waters seek your way;
Seeing mountains clear, your heart holds sway.

Blame not if my view is flawed;
The mind itself breeds the disease.
Narrow and closed, the heart is awed;
The true person finds no demons to appease.

Wealth and steed in gallant race;
The man of ambition finds his place.
Prepare your journey early on;
Return with honor, live long and fond.

The noble rise, while petty ones block;
Struggles bring the pain of parting.
Ahead, a benefactor awaits;
Trust in messages, horses and oxen, a person in Chu.
All matters require careful planning.

The boat leaves the ancient ferry, the moon leaves the clouds;
One exits Tong Pass and may well ask the way.
Go forward and seek a place to settle;
Why harbor doubts and a hesitant mind?

Swords and halberds line the mountain forest;
thieves and robbers will surely invade.
Defeated and fleeing, then capture and search brings settlement;
ennobled, blessing descendants.

The shore is wide, the water deep, the boat easily falls;
the road is long, the mountains steep, steps are hard.
Yet the snake crawls and eventually finds a crossing;
the moon rises in the sky, extraordinarily bright.

Autumn frost harsh, summer sun fierce;
New flowers bloom, old ones fade.
The world's warmth and cold you see;
Meeting one, no words need be said.

Easy not easy, hard not hard;
Suddenly waves arise,
Laughter just a few times.

A tiger crouches on the road ahead;
O traveler, do not call or shout.
Walk with care along the path's edge;
Then calamities will naturally fade out.

Magpies chatter before the eaves, dancing gracefully;
Worries vanish completely, joy arises naturally.
One person advances, another retreats;
In the end, there is still a harmonious marital bond.

Advantage lies in central lands, go to war;
Capturing chieftains at the royal court.
Phoenix bearing crimson decree returns to sunny shore;
Enjoy a fine name, glory across the four seas.

A youth early learned at the courtly gate;
Long has the azure path been his quest.
A benefactor arrives to aid his fate;
Flowers fade, yet seeds form—the harvest is blessed.

One mind on two things, one thing with two minds;
New blossoms on withered trees,
Wait till spring intertwines.

Do not say things are without flaw;
Amidst it, advances and retreats are many.
The cassia wheel rounds then wanes;
Its luster must be polished again.

Do not sigh that matters delay;
Do not say they will never reach their end.
The long rod will finally be in hand;
With one cast, a golden hook brings the catch.

When matters seem ripe, still guard against pitfalls;
Lest before acting, you stumble first.
If you wish to go, then hold back a while;
You must still rely on the strength of allies.

Fierce wind blows ink-black clouds flying;
The moon at the sky's heart cannot be hidden.
In idle hours, nothing matters;
In the end, no harm or loss.

Above and below, harmony is gone;
Labor expended, yet nothing is won.
Step out the door to the open way;
From this, the start and end shall stay.

Matters proceed, worry not nor fret;
Spring wind brings joy, naturally met.
A longer line of three feet cast;
Pleased, you'll catch fresh fish at last.

Round then waning, waning then round;
Low and dense, you must maneuver with care.
When the time comes, at last the bond appears.

Haggard, with no one to ask;
In the forest, listening to the cuckoo.
A mountain moon and a flute's sound;
A thousand li of tears, trickling on.

Amid lotus fragrance, deep grace is received;
When the cassia moon rounds, a new seal is bound.
From this day, your famed name weighs as mountains and peaks;
Your brilliant light ascends to the highest decree.

Flowers fall when spring is here;
The traveler is halfway on the way.
Matters approach completion yet not done;
Entanglements linger for twenty or thirty days.

In the deep pool, fish can be caught;
In the quiet valley, birds can be netted.
Only use a lasting heart;
Do not give rise to doubt.

Darkness fades, brightness emerges;
Worrisome matters may find harmony;
In the end, all becomes a smile;
For now, cease doubting and guessing.

The precious mirror is unstained by dust;
The golden marten has been tailored;
It also meets the accord of Heaven;
In the end, no dust will cling.

Matters of harmony,
Achieved with laughter;
Joyful news comes halfway;
Step by step, you walk on azure clouds.

Flowers wither, the moon wanes;
The mirror is shattered, the hairpin parted;
Cease coming and going;
Then matters begin to be at peace.

From nothingness, uprightness shall arise;
Your cares may turn to sorrow, yet be wise.
Clouds part, the moon returns to full in skies;
A thousand miles, the urgent sail boat flies.

Creation's course is nature's own design;
A thousand-mile campaign brings blessings line by line.
Success in fame with divine aid is shown;
When Snake meets Rabbit, change will then be known.

Rely on mighty power, all demons disappear;
Yet after vanquishing, maintain the power near.
Exert the might with all your strength;
Remember well, lest you fall at length.

The Way demands a steadfast heart; with steadfast heart, the Way is earned.
Achieve great deeds, then early depart;
Build a thatched hut, refine your inner art;
One day you soar, immortal's rank you'll own.

A sheep leaves the flock, facing the people day by day;
When it meets an ox's mouth, it bites.
One lord, one minister—lord and minister are startled;
They must rely on the true spirit to save the multitudes.

Bloom and decay are long set – do not sigh;
Toil in other lands, yet find peace at home.
Sewing bridal gowns for others to wear;
Today you taste it, tomorrow another shall share.

Southeast and North shall turn into ruins;
The land of Yanji sees no sustenance for its people;
If you wish to rouse great ambition,
Where is the source of water?

Within lies a mystical verse;
At cockcrow it will emerge.
Suddenly grasp the Zen gate;
Break through the sovereign's gate path.

Several goldfish take the bait;
The silk rod pulls back.
Home food seems too costly;
Roam the five lakes and four seas.

At Mao hour, the child leaves the forest;
At noon hour, fortune arrives.
Mao is born from Yin;
Then Heaven's heart is seen.

The water clock urges the rooster's crow;
Travelers hasten, forming a line.
Late at night, crossing the ferry and pass;
Boundless prospects lie ahead.

Rise and go, rise and go;
Head forward and form alliances.
With one hand lift the pillar of heaven;
Your name will shine in history.

A child grows, forming the Water pattern;
When Fire arrives in time, fortune returns.
Do not be overly anxious;
The human heart's discontent knows no bounds.

A guest goose circles the lake, now turned to land; 
Having achieved merit, return early while you can. 
Greed and attachment are not lasting bliss; 
Do not let the fowls and ducks squabble in vain.

There is a petty person here;
Do not tarry even a moment.
Pack up quickly, set out soon;
Time flies like the sun and moon, do not linger long.

After morning rain clears, the jade stream gleams;
Layer upon layer of spring hues climb the wicker gate.
Gold never ends, the family is rich and abundant;
Why envy the mere finery of brocade robes?

Mountains end, roads turn maze;
Rapids rush, boats hardly cross.
Do not force any matter;
Every move meets envy and spite.

Times change and bring many hardships, with trembling and fear;
Cautious and frightened, as if walking on thin ice.
You must recognize the dangers and risks ahead;
A single lamp in a cage amidst a gust of wind.

Heaven remembers those who toil in earnest;
They will never sink into the mundane world.
A pure heart can perceive the Way;
Distractions and turmoil only lose the true spirit.
